    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-06-21T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-06-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="20"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d20">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">
                    <persName corresp="#p_HHL1">Hopkins</persName> Papers</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chinese Minister of Foreign Affairs</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_STV1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Soong</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Presidents Special Assistant</hi>
                        (<persName corresp="#p_HHL1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hopkins</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="1" xml:id="d20fn1">The source is handwritten.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-06-21">21st July,
                            1943</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Dear <persName corresp="#p_HHL1">Harry</persName>
                    </hi>
                </p>
                <p>My departure has been delayed till tomorrow morning owing to engine trouble.</p>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Generalissimo1">Generalissimo</gloss> cabled me that it would
                    be awkward for United Nations’ relations, and Sino-Russian relations in
                    particular, if he goes thru Siberia without seeing <persName corresp="#p_SIV1"
                        >Stalin</persName>. Therefore he prefers the rendezvous to be somewhere else
                    than Alaska.</p>
                <p>If the President desires to advance the date of the meeting to some time in
                    August or September, he would be able to make it, provided he is given two
                    weeks’ notice.<note n="2" xml:id="d20fn2">No reply to this message has been
                        found, but presumably <persName corresp="#p_CKS1">Chiang</persName> was told
                        that it would not be possible to arrange the meeting until autumn.</note>
                </p>
                <p>He requests me to proceed to London according to programme, but to be in
                    readiness to return &amp; participate in the Conference whenever the President
                    desires it.</p>
                <p>Hoping that you will have a nice little rest in New Hampshire</p>
                <p>Sincerely,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_STV1">T. V. [<hi rend="smallcaps"
                            >Soong</hi>]</persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
